WHO   — PLAYSTATION VITA — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown
WHAT  — The Vita was a genuine pocket powerhouse — a quad-core ARM CPU, a quad-core GPU, a vivid OLED screen, dual analog sticks, and front-and-rear touch. Technically superb and beloved by a devoted base, it was undercut by expensive proprietary memory cards and the rise of phone gaming.
